story.title: Riddle Me This - Episode 1
story.storyDescription: Isabelle: Did you make me a scavenger hunt?
story.creator: web-uploader

messages.text: Did you make me a scavenger hunt?
I have no idea what you’re talking about.
When I got back to my dorm from my evening class…
There was a note on my message board.
I think it’s the first one in a scavenger hunt.
What does it say?
“Finding the first clue will be a treat. Look for it where you eat.”
Did you check the fridge?
Yeah, and there was another clue there. Along with a piece of cheesecake.
Yum! What did the note say?
That’s not the point!
I want to know who did this.
Well it wasn’t me.
Did you ask Kinslee?
Yes. And Jade and Taylor and the rest of the Delta Gamma girls.
Each of them said she didn’t do it.
Hmm. Well it beats me.
Ugh. This is so creepy. Someone was inside my dorm room!
People are inside your dorm room all the time LOL
It’s party central over there.
Hey! I haven’t had a party in two weeks.
And this clue wasn’t here this morning.
Someone was in here while I was in class 🙁
Are you sure?
Hello? There are notes here. It’s obvious.
OK, well did your roommate do it?
Sarah “Please Turn it Down” Bukowski?
Good point. Sarah would never have that much fun.
I still can’t believe she got into Delta Gamma.
Or that she made it through that crazy rush week…
She only got in because her mom was a fellow sister.
I know. That Legacy rule is so outdated.
Ok, so Sarah didn’t make the scavenger hunt…
But maybe she let in whoever did?
Maybe you have a secret admirer?
Oh! What if it’s that hot guy from Comparative Lit?
I highly doubt Ethan was in my dorm room.
Why not? You know he has a crush on you.
Plus he’s always doing those weird crossword puzzles in class.
That’s true…
Well there’s only one way to find out if it was him.
DO THE SCAVENGER HUNT!
I’m sure you’ll figure out who it is by the end.
And then maybe… 😘 🎆
That does sound appealing…
That’s the spirit!
What does the next clue say?
“Now that you’re fed, look for a clue where you lay your pretty head.”
See? PRETTY head?
It’s definitely a secret admirer! It’s gotta be Ethan.
Did you check your bed?
Isabelle walks over to her bed.
On first glance, she doesn’t see anything unusual.
But then she peels back her covers.
She gasps.
Um…
What??
There are rose petals on my sheets.
OMG!
This is kind of creepy, don’t you think?
I think it’s romantic!
What does the next clue say?
“When you use your next gift you’ll be under arrest. They’re furry too, in case you hadn’t guessed.”
Hmm 🤔
Handcuffs?
Isabelle does a quick sweep of her room.
Finding nothing, she opens her closet…and freezes.
Hanging inside is a black bustier.
A pair of hot pink, fuzzy handcuffs are draped over the hanger.
They’re handcuffs all right…
I just found them in my closet. Along with some lingerie 😳
Good lord, Ethan. I like this guy’s style!
We don’t know that it’s Ethan. It could be some creep.
And even if it is Ethan…this is still a little creepy.
It’s totally him!
What does the next clue say?
“Roll these and your dreams may come true. Whatever they say, I will do.”
That’s a tough one.
Well I just figured it out.
Isabelle texts Emily a picture of the sexy dice she found on her desk.
Ethan, you minx!
I don’t know. This is all a bit much.
I mean, he could have started with flowers or something.
Flowers are boring. Don’t be a party pooper!
What does the next clue say?
“You’re getting close, now go outside. It’s on the thing you use to drive.”
Eeek! He’s totally going to be out there!
Go get your man!
Are you kidding me? I am NOT going outside.
Why not?
Because it’s dark out.
And I parked in the back lot.
And someone was inside my room tonight.
Plus, we don’t know that it’s Ethan.
True…
But who else would it be?
Come on, aren’t you dying to know what the next clue says?
And what if it IS Ethan and he’s waiting outside for you?
What if it’s an ax murder?
LOL it’s not an ax murderer.
But ask campus security to go with you if you’re that nervous.
Campus security is kind of mad at me after that last party…
Can you blame them?
That party was out of control! Poor Sarah.
What do you mean “poor Sarah”?
I warned her I was having a party.
I just felt a bit bad for her trying to study with those big headphones on.
She could have gone to the library to study!
She was just trying to make a point.
I know. Anyway, what are you going to do about this clue?
I don’t know…
You’re right. It is a tough choice…
Meet your secret admirer, or study for the Comp Lit exam.
Well when you put it that way LOL
Isabelle grabs her keys and walks down to the dark parking lot.
OK, I’m at my car.
And???
And no Ethan 🙁
BOO!
There was a clue under my windshield wipers…
It says “Clue #6 will soon be found. All you have to do is turn around.”
Well?
That’s it. There’s no other clue here.
And no secret admirer.
Hmm. Maybe the next clue blew away in the wind?
I don’t know, but I’m going back to my room.
Awww! Are you sure you haven’t missed the clue?
Isabelle is out of patience. She turns around to walk back to her dorm—
But someone grabs her from behind.
She tries to scream, but a hand clamps over her mouth.
Hello? Are you there?
OK, I’m starting to freak out here.
If you don’t answer me I’m going to call Campus Security.
Two minutes later
Sarah, did you get her?
Yeah. She fought us pretty hard though.
It took three of us to get her tied up.  She almost got away.
Sorry. There was a sedative in the cake but I don’t think she ate it.
I couldn’t force the issue or it would have been obvious something was up.
It was hard enough to get her to do the scavenger hunt.
Where is she now?
Gagged and hogtied in the back of Kinslee’s car.
On the way to the barn. Just like the plan…
Great!
I don’t feel great. I feel sick.
Just remember why we’re doing this, Sarah.
Remember what she did to you.
What she did to ALL of us.
I know…
Isabelle has been ruining our sorority’s reputation with all those parties.
She’s been terrorizing pledges for years.
And she’ll keep doing it too.
Unless someone stops her.
She has to be taught a lesson.
What if we get caught? I don’t want to go to jail.
Relax! No one’s going to jail.
And it isn’t like we’re going to kill her.
We’re just humiliating her, the way she did to us during pledge week.
I guess…
You did a good thing, Sarah.
Now go enjoy your quiet dorm room!
You have the whole place to yourself for the next seven days.
Seven days?!
That’s how long rush week was, right? 😈
